member.remarks:
This method allows registering a new contact.
Example request:
POST /api/Contacts/Create { "Name": "New Contact", "Email": "email@example.com" }

This method allows updating the data of a contact in the system.
Example request:
PUT /api/Contacts/Update { "ContactId": 123, "Name": "New Name", "Email": "newemail@example.com" }

This method updates the status of a contact, closes the related process, removes associated events, and logs an action of type "Blacklist". It also synchronizes the contact's status in the database.
Example request:
PUT /api/Contacts/AddToBlacklist { "ContactId": 123, "NewContactStatusId": 2, "NewStatusReason": "Reason for change", "NewStatusObservations": "Additional observations", "ProcessId": 456 }

This method adds a course to the favorites list if is true, or removes it if false. The course's status is updated in the database.
Example request:
PUT /api/Courses/AddCourseToFavourite { "ContactLeadId": 123, "ProcessId": 456, "CourseFavourite": true }

This method creates a new lead contact in the database. If the course country is not found, an exception is thrown.
Example request:
POST /api/Leads { "PhonePrefix": "1", "Phone": "5551234567", "Email": "example@example.com", "CourseCountryId": 1, "University": "TechUniversity", "CourseId": 123, "ContactId": 456, "IsFavourite": true, "Types": [ "Recommended", "OtherType" ], "StartDateCourse": "2024-01-01", "FinishDateCourse": "2024-12-31" }

This method adds the specified faculties to the contact in the database. If the contact is not found, an exception is thrown.
Example request:
POST /api/Faculties { "ContactId": 123, "FacultiesId": [1, 2, 3] }

This method removes the specified faculty from the contact in the database. If the contact is not found, an exception is thrown.
Example request:
DELETE /api/Faculty { "FacultyId": 1, "ContactId": 123 }

This method adds the specified specialties to the contact in the database. If the contact is not found, an exception is thrown.
Example request:
POST /api/Specialities { "ContactId": 123, "SpecialitiesId": [1, 2, 3] }

This method removes the specified specialties from the contact in the database. If the contact is not found, an exception is thrown.
Example request:
DELETE /api/Specialities { "ContactId": 123, "SpecialitiesId": [1, 2, 3] }

This method adds a new email address to the contact in the database. If the contact is not found or if the email address already exists, an exception is thrown.
Example request:
POST /api/AddEmailContact { "ContactId": 123, "Email": "example@example.com", "EmailTypeId": 1, "IsDefault": true }

This method updates the country code of the contact in the database. If the contact is not found, an exception is thrown.
Example request:
PUT /api/UpdateCountryCode { "CountryCode": "US", "ContactId": 123 }

This method updates the currency of the contact in the database. If the contact is not found, an exception is thrown.
Example request:
PUT /api/UpdateCurrency { "CurrencyId": 1, "ContactId": 123 }

This method updates the information of the lead contact in the database. If the identifier of the lead contact does not match that of the command, a bad request error is returned. If the lead contact is not found, an error code is returned.
Example request:
PUT /api/ContactLead/123 { "ContactLeadId": 123, "Discount": 10, "FinalPrice": 200, "EnrollmentPercentage": 50, "Fees": 5, "CourseTypeBaseCode": "CT001", "StartDateCourse": "2023-01-01", "FinishDateCourse": "2023-12-31", "ConvocationDate": "2023-12-01", "CourseCode": "C001", "Types": [1, 2, 3] }

This method updates the information of the lead contacts in the database.
Example request:
PUT /api/ContactLeads { "ContactLeads": [ { "ContactLeadId": 1, "Discount": 10, "FinalPrice": 200, "EnrollmentPercentage": 50, "Fees": 5, "CourseTypeBaseCode": "CT001", "StartDateCourse": "2023-01-01", "FinishDateCourse": "2023-12-31", "ConvocationDate": "2023-12-01", "Types": [1, 2] }, { "ContactLeadId": 2, "Discount": 15, "FinalPrice": 250, "EnrollmentPercentage": 60, "Fees": 10, "CourseTypeBaseCode": "CT002", "StartDateCourse": "2023-02-01", "FinishDateCourse": "2023-11-30", "ConvocationDate": "2023-11-15", "Types": [2, 3] } ] }

This method updates the price of the lead contact in the database. If the identifier of the lead contact does not match that of the command, a bad request error is returned. If the lead contact is not found, an error code is returned.
Example request:
PUT /api/ContactLeadPrice/123 { "ContactLeadId": 123, "Discount": 10, "Price": 150, "FinalPrice": 140, "EnrollmentPercentage": 50, "Fees": 5 }

This method sends a command to copy the contact information to a FP coupon.
Example request:
POST /api/CopyToCouponFp { "ContactId": 123, "ProcessId": 456 }

This method queries the database to retrieve the details of the email that matches the provided identifier.

Example request:

    GET /api/emails/{id}

This method queries the database to fetch the signature associated with the provided corporate email.

Example request:

    GET /api/Signatures/{corporateEmail}

This method allows updating an existing invoice payment option in the database.

Example request:

    PUT /api/{id}

This method allows deleting an invoice payment option from the database by marking it as deleted.

Example request:

    DELETE /api/{id}

Example request:
POST /api/orders-imported/Tlmk { "ApiKey": "api-key", "NumPedido": "12345", "Nombre": "Juan Prez", "Email": "juan.perez@example.com", "Titulo": "Programming Course" }
Returns the ID of the created imported order. If the order data is invalid. If the user is not authorized to perform this operation. If an internal server error occurs.

Example request:
PUT /api/orders-imported/SetProcessStatusByOrderNumber { "OrderNumber": 12345, "Status": "Completed", "Outcome": "Success", "PaymentType": "CreditCard" }
Returns a string indicating that the operation was successful. If the provided data is invalid. If no order or process associated with the specified order number is found. If an internal server error occurs.

Example request:
DELETE /api/orders-imported/DeleteOrderImportedFromTlmkByEmail { "Emails": ["email1@example.com", "email2@example.com"] }
Returns a list of IDs of the deleted orders. If the provided data is invalid. If the user is not authorized to perform this operation. If an internal server error occurs.

Example request:
POST /api/template-proposal { "Name": "Template Proposal 1", "ProcessType": "ProcessType", "Day": 5, "Attempt": 3, "Colour": "#FF5733", "CourseKnown": true, "CourseTypeId": 10, "HasToSendEmail": true, "HasToSendWhatsApp": false, "TagId": 2 }
Returns the ID of the successfully created template proposal. If the provided data is invalid. If a necessary resource such as Tag or CourseType is not found. If the user is not authorized to perform this operation. If an internal server error occurs.

Example request:
PUT /api/template-proposal/1 { "Id": 1, "Name": "Updated Template Proposal", "ProcessType": "NewProcessType", "Day": 10, "Attempt": 2, "Colour": "#3366FF", "CourseKnown": false, "CourseTypeId": 15, "HasToSendEmail": false, "HasToSendWhatsApp": true, "TagId": 3 }
Indicates that the template proposal was successfully updated. If the provided ID does not match the ID in the command or if the data is invalid. If the template proposal or any associated resource such as Tag or CourseType is not found. If the user is not authorized to perform this operation. If an internal server error occurs.

This endpoint obtains the seller ID (`IdVendedor`) linked to the email of the authenticated user.
**Example request:** GET /api/users/GetCurrentUser SellerId Headers: Authorization: Bearer {token}
**Expected responses:** - `200 OK`: Returns the associated seller ID. - `401 Unauthorized`: If the user is not authenticated. - `500 Internal Server Error`: If an internal error occurred.
